  "footnotes": [
    "Kruševo Republic: A 10-day revolutionary commune proclaimed during the Ilinden–Preobrazhenie Uprising (2–12 August 1903); crushed by Ottoman forces.",
    "Independent State of Macedonia: Short-lived Axis-affiliated state proclaimed in September 1944; collapsed with Yugoslav liberation in November 1944.",
    "WWII division: Western districts (Tetovo, Debar) were annexed to Italian-controlled Albanian state; most of the territory was occupied by the Kingdom of Bulgaria.",
    "Macedonian naming dispute: The country used 'Republic of Macedonia' from 1991 until 2019, when the Prespa Agreement with Greece led to adoption of 'North Macedonia'."
